profile_positions.description:
A member of Plan&Manage Finance team in a large scale project to implement a new ERP platform and supporting integrations. Primary role is to liaise with finance controllers and operations to identify Pan-European business requirements, analyse and elaborate them with IT to find an optimal system architecture and ensure that developed solutions are fit to business. In addition, the role encompasses:

- BPM - business process analysis and mapping in ARIS to align with (strategic) marketing, supply chain, master data, service and other areas to ensure an end-to-end process flow compatible with all system integrations and supporting processes;
- Business process scoping in relation to the targets of the project;
- Elaborating business requirements with solution architects, tracking component delivery to facilitate accurate reporting on project and solution development;
- Cross-disciplinary workshops with domain process owners, consultants and solution architects to find an optimal point between business process improvement, system capabilities, feasibility, costs and change management;
- Identifying business impact and documenting material used for training, SIT and UAT.

Skills, knowledge and achievements:
- 4 years of experience with various Oracle modules
- Oracle R12 implementation and roll-out support in European sales companies
- Exposure to Oracle R12, Hyperion, CPQ, salesforce.com, Steelwedge, ICON and other system integrations supporting various business activities
- Proposed an EMEA wide pricing/discount solution to improve process efficiency /cash position of Canon companies
- Business/IT Requirement gathering and solution elaboration on end-to-end process integrations between budgeting, financial operations, consolidation, supply chain operations, sales and other supporting applications/business activities
- Negotiation between controllers, IT consultants/developers and project management on solution feasibility
